// Plan 159 Ф.1 NEGATIVE (guard regression): a `main`-less module is a LIBRARY,
// not an executable — there is no entry point to anchor reachability against, so
// the "no main → keep everything" guard fires and NOTHING is pruned, even free
// functions with no live caller (`unreachable_helper`, reached only by the
// exported `api`, which is itself never called here).
//
// We cannot link a library (no `main`), so the test asserts the ONLY missing
// symbol is `nova_fn_main_impl`. Crucially it must NOT be a pruned helper: if
// reachability DCE had (wrongly) run in library mode, `unreachable_helper` would
// be dropped and the link error would name IT instead. Codegen succeeding and
// emitting every helper is the proof of non-pruning. (The complementary unit
// test `exported_fn_in_library_mode_is_kept` asserts the empty dead-set
// directly.)
// EXPECT_CC_ERROR nova_fn_main_impl

module plan159.neg_library_not_pruned

// No live caller anywhere in this module — kept only because library mode
// disables pruning entirely.
fn unreachable_helper() -> int {
    424242
}

export fn api() -> int {
    unreachable_helper()
}
